This paper deals with the computational complexity of computing boolean functions using various models such as decision trees, formulas, and branching programs. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses efficient algorithms and proofs, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the study of complexity theory and computational models could also be relevant to scientific computing (cs.SC).
